<unit id="4566d44d-44e5-4bf8-87b8-f29d4ecaaa03">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 2</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: # </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Resource Monitor</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="e250d8eb-dbf6-4524-8b56-4c181d36e9f3">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 4</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Authors: Alex Hall, Joseph Lee, Kefas Lungu, Beqa Gozalishvili, Tuukka Ojala, Ethin Probst, Kevin Derome and other NVDA contributors</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="4ba3b2ea-5e7e-4236-9e69-d99ce0e70168">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 6</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This add-on gives information about CPU load, memory usage and other resource usage information.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="10cb3779-3d16-4d8b-a57e-36391bdd69e8">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 8</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Shortcuts</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="756f97fb-9153-48a2-83ca-6bc45c455fa1">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 10</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>All commands support speech on demand mode.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="423b28c0-164b-4add-a208-4a2e3adb4bcc">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 12</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+Shift+E: presents used RAM (pyysical memory) and average processor load.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a026e904-4609-43d5-8864-ad078a2e219d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 13</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+Shift+1: presents the average processor load and if multicore CPU's are present the load of each core.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="47a09da1-230e-4a42-adc5-6d417147197e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 14</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+Shift+2/5: presents the used and total space for both physical and virtual RAM (NVDA+Shift+5 is an alternative to NVDA+Shift+2 when the latter keyboard combination cannot be performed).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="9ba2e8c0-8a34-4db0-a2a7-3cedaaa63510">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 15</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+Shift+3: presents the used and total space of the fixed (built-in) and removable drives.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="db7950ec-fe1c-455d-8906-e2a42e87520b">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 16</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+Shift+4: presents information on the wireless connection, network (SSID) name and strength, or no SSID if there is none available.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="506384aa-e388-4416-8b62-bb1ba9c9f41d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 17</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+Shift+6: presents  Windows version, CPU architecture, and exact build number (build.revision).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="6b242ca4-370e-473c-9c2c-e2d6db09aa5d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 18</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+Shift+7: presents the system's uptime.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="7556990e-9fd3-4d08-b63e-80995af1ae42">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 19</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Unassigned: presents information about the graphics processing unit (GPU; unavailable in secure mode).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="59eb243e-d5cd-4530-8309-13acf93213a2">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 21</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>You can change these shortcut keys via input gestures dialog.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="cf9d1f4c-49a9-44c6-b161-ecfd913e64f6">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 23</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Usage notes</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="6afdbb36-1fa8-4498-99e0-3af26ac88091">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 25</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This add-on does not replace task manager and other system information programs for Windows. Also note the following:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="37591af6-d9cc-43d2-b8e5-e72ac286e8a9">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 27</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Apart from overall resource usage command (NVDA+Shift+E), pressing other commands twice will copy resource usage information to the clipboard.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="70ea07e4-d172-4dc7-aa11-970495a5c25e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 28</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Resource information cannot be copied to the clipboard if running the add-on in secure screens.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="3c1109cf-caa1-4f20-8801-a032bbcdecbc">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 29</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>CPU usage is given for logical processors, not physical cores. This is noticeable for processors which uses Hyper-Threading where number of CPU's is twice the number of CPU cores. On some newer computers, not all CPU cores will have hyper-threading enabled.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="76de1c68-d3d8-4811-8462-83397bb45d53">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 30</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>If there is heavy disk activity such as copying large files, there might be delays when obtaining disk usage information.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="7fe4f01c-c276-4cd6-bd70-9946b79e26d6">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 31</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>When announcing processor architecture information, "x86" and "AMD64" refer to 32-bit and 64-bit (x64) Intel and AMD processors, respectively.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="2526a96e-9263-4d2b-acf3-adf0ebf773e0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 32</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Installing the add-on on Windows 10/11 LTSC is not supported.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="cede3681-25e1-4335-adad-b188883c418e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 34</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>For a list of changes made between each add-on releases, refer to [changelogs for add-on releases][1] document.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="32d59eb2-cc6d-4498-8a04-ed6e06dbe82e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 36</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>[1]: https://github.com/kefaslungu/resourceMonitor/blob/main/changes.md</source>
</segment>
</unit>
